.:: Puzzle 2x6-Level-5-5::.
6 different games are played: monopoly, snooker, whist, go, chess, scrabble
The people prefer 6 different types of sport: badminton, basketball, cricket, ice-hockey, skiing, soccer
 1. the person playing go is on the left or right of the person who's sport is basketball##3
 2. the person playing whist is on the far left or far right##3
 3. the person playing chess is somewhere to the left of the person who's sport is skiing##5
 4. the person who's sport is badminton is on the left of the person playing chess##1
 5. the person who's sport is skiing is in an odd position##4
 6. the person who's sport is soccer is the person playing go##1
 7. the person playing scrabble is on the right of the person playing monopoly##1
 8. the person playing scrabble is somewhere to the left of the person playing chess##5
 9. the person playing chess is on the left or right of the person playing scrabble##3
10. the person who's sport is ice-hockey is the person playing whist##1
11. the person playing monopoly is in an even position##4
12. the person who's sport is badminton is somewhere to the left of the person playing whist##5

.:: Answer ::.
|               |    1    |     2      |     3     |      4      |   5    |     6      |
| Game   | go | monopoly     | scrabble    | chess | snooker | whist    |
| Sport         | soccer  | basketball | badminton | cricket     | skiing | ice-hockey |

