.:: Puzzle 2x6-Level-5-9::.
City: venice, san-francisco, paris, edinburgh, boston, hamburg
The people use 6 different means of transport: bike, bus, snowmobile, subway, tram, van
 1. the person traveling to edinburgh is somewhere to the left of the person traveling to boston##5
 2. the person driving the bike is on the right of the person driving the tram##1
 3. the person driving the bike is on the left or right of the person traveling to boston##3
 4. the person driving the subway is on the left or right of the person driving the van##3
 5. the person traveling to venice is the person traveling to venice##1
 6. the person traveling to boston is somewhere to the left of the person driving the subway##5
 7. the person driving the subway is on the right of the person traveling to paris##1
 8. the person traveling to hamburg is somewhere to the right of the person traveling to boston##5
 9. the person traveling to venice is somewhere to the right of the person driving the bike##5
10. the person traveling to hamburg is between the person traveling to paris and the person driving the van##2
11. the person driving the snowmobile is on the left of the person traveling to hamburg##1
12. the person driving the tram is on the left of the person traveling to san-francisco##1
13. the person traveling to hamburg is somewhere to the right of the person traveling to paris##5
14. the person traveling to edinburgh is somewhere to the left of the person traveling to hamburg##5
15. the person driving the bus is in an odd position##4
16. the person driving the bike is in an even position##4

.:: Answer ::.
|               |   1   |     2     |    3     |     4      |    5    |   6    |
| City   | edinburgh | san-francisco | boston | paris     | hamburg | venice |
| Transport     | tram  | bike      | bus      | snowmobile | subway  | van    |

